This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new resolution algorithm for tensor decomposition that targets deep learning optimizer algorithms. Additionally, the paper uses state-of-the-art deep learning gradient optimization models in its experiments. 

The paper also involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) as it uses gradient and Hessian-vector product to ensure convergence during optimization. 

Data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) is another likely sub-category as tensor decomposition involves factorization techniques for multidimensional arrays. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI) are also possible sub-categories as tensor decomposition is a powerful tool for scientific analysis and can be applied to various fields such as image processing, natural language processing, and social network analysis.
